Items.Name: Wood Tools Level 2

Items.Description:
Take your wood working skills for a spin on this beginner friendly planter workshop. Over the course of two sessions, participants will make a window planter for 6 pots featuring lap joints, edges profiled with a router, and evenly drilled holes.

Learning Outcomes:
- Practice repeatable, safe cuts on the table saw
- Learn various joinery techniques including cutting dado’s to create lap joints
- Advance your table saw knowledge with dado cuts, and the cross-cut sled
- Practice using the drill press, the table router, and various sanding methods to finish your planter
Items.Name: Planter Workshop

Items.Description:
This more advanced woodworking course will cover the use of the jointer, planer, table saw, wide belt sander and biscuit jointer. Over the course of three sessions participants will walk away with a cutting board and their certification for Wood Tools 2.

Learning Objectives:

- Safe use of machine tools (including jointer, planer, table saw and biscuit jointer)

- Wood grain education

- Breakout and surfacing of rough sawn solid wood

- Cutting curved shapes using a template and router

Once sanded you can opt for a laser cut image on your board! Ask your instructor for available designs, or design your own and take the Laser Cutter Level 1 Class to put your own image on it.

Things to bring:

PPE including:

  • Safety glasses

  • Hearing protection

  • Closed toe shoes

  • Remove jewelry

  • Tie back long hair 

  • No loose clothing

  • Dust mask (optional)
